# Web UI Layout

- Prefer full-width page and dashboard layouts that use the available viewport.
- Do not add centered container wrappers such as `mx-auto max-w-*` for primary
  app chrome, dashboard pages, data views, cards, or tables.
- Keep focused pages compact when that is the natural shape of the task, such as
  sign-in, setup, confirmation, and short single-form flows.
- Use narrow widths for controls or content that need an intrinsic size to work
  well, such as small buttons, badges, icons, compact form fields, and short
  readable copy.
